\h TASTE \d

\uUSAGE\n
!taste thing

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Taste a) an item in your inventory, or b) an item in your readied equipment.

Provide a single argument indicating what you'd like to taste. If you indicate a vessel, you will taste the liquid contents of that vessel.

You may only taste one thing at a time.

To taste the bread in your inventory:
\qtaste \li#l\qbread\d4`
...or just...
\qtaste bread\d4`

To taste the ring in your readied equipment:
\qtaste \le#l\qring\d4`

To taste the liquid contents of the flask in your inventory:
\qtaste \li#l\qflask\d4`
...or just...
\qtaste flask\d4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
abbreviation, drink, eat, equipment, inventory, listen, look, lookself, prefixes, roomfixtures, smell
